'''Felix A. Chami''' is an [[archaeologist]] from [[Tanzania]]. He is a [[professor]] at [[University of Dar es Salaam|Dar es Salaam University]]. Dr. Chami discovered, on the island of Mafia and Juani, artefacts that revealed [[East Africa]] as being integral to the [[Indian Ocean trade]].<ref>Shubart, Tira.[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/1924318.stm Tanzanian dig unearths ancient secret]. BBC News: Wednesday, 17 April 2002, 17:27 GMT 18:27 UK</ref>
